msgid "If you want to produce cut out shapes with *exact* dimensions after the burn, then you need to take half the width of the laserbeam into consideration (aka Kerf compensation).\nThis routine will create a couple of test shapes for you to establish this value.\nAfter you cut these shapes out you need to try to fit the shapes with the same label together. Choose the pair that has a perfect fit and use the label as your kerf-compensation value."
